Ruby and Alpha Sapphire}}.\n* Hoopa Unbound is the only Pokémon with a {{cat|Pokémon with a base stat total of 680|base stat total of 680}} that is not a [[Legendary Pokémon]].\n* In [[Pokémon Omega Ruby and Alpha Sapphire]], the "mysterious rings" in [[mirage spot]]s, from which Pokémon jump out when interacted with, resemble rings used by Hoopa.\n\n===Origin===\nHoopa Confined may have been inspired by common depictions of {{wp|jinn|djinn}}, particularly those with wisp-like tails. Its having rings around its wrists could have been inspired by the djinn in the story of {{wp|Aladdin}}.\n\nHoopa Unbound may also have been inspired by djinn, while its six arms may be drawn from the Hindu deities known as {{wp|Shakti}}, who were rumored to grow multiple arms. It may also be based on the {{wp|Gegenees}}, who were a tribe of six-armed giants who fought the {{wp|Argonauts}} in {{wp|Greek mythology}}. Its tail and horns may also derive from common depictions of demons.\n\nBoth forms of Hoopa could also be partly based on the legend of {{wp|Nezha}}, a deity worshiped in {{wp|Taoism}} and {{wp|Chinese folk religion}} and commonly referred to as a trickster deity and a worldly protector. Very much like Hoopa Unbound, Nezha is depicted holding rings and is sometimes depicted with multiple arms. Its ability to use its hoops to transport things may be based on {{wp|Portals in fiction|portals}}.\n\nIts relationship with the [[Prison Bottle]] is similar to the djinn\'s with its lamp in traditional Arabian stories, since its full power is sealed within its respective vessel. Hoopa\'s only being able to maintain its Unbound state for three days parallels the limit to the number of wishes a djinni can grant to its current master. In both Formes, its Shiny coloration reflects on the Arabian origins of djinn.\n\n====Name origin====\nHoopa is derived from \'\'hoop\'\'. It may also be derived from \'\'hoopla\'\' (something loud, attention-grabbing, and possibly misleading).\n\n==In other languages==\n{{Other languages|type=psychic|type2=Ghost\n|ja=フーパ \'\'Hoopa\'\'|jameaning=From \'\'hoop\'\' and possibly \'\'hoopla\'\'\n|fr=Hoopa|frmeaning=Same as Japanese name\n|es=Hoopa|esmeaning=Same as Japanese name\n|de=Hoopa|demeaning=Same as Japanese name\n|it=Hoopa|itmeaning=Same as Japanese name\n|ko=후파 \'\'Hoopa\'\'|komeaning=Transliteration of its Japanese name\n|zh_yue=胡帕 \'\'Wùhpaak\'\'|zh_yuemeaning=Mandarin-based transliteration of its Japanese name. Contains {{tt|胡 \'\'wùh\'\'|recklessly}}.\n|zh_cmn=胡帕 \'\'Húpà\'\'|zh_cmnmeaning=Transliteration of its Japanese name. Contains {{tt|胡 \'\'hú\'\'|recklessly}}.\n|el=Χούπα \'\'Khoúpa\'\'|elmeaning=Transcription of English name\n|hi=हूपा \'\'Hoopa\'\'|himeaning=Transcription of English name\n|ru=Хуппа \'\'Khuppa\'\'|rumeaning=Transcription of English name\n}}\n{{-}}\n{| style="float:left"\n|-\n| style="vertical-align:top" |\n\'\'Hoopa Confined\'\'\n{{langtable\n|color={{psychic color}}|bordercolor={{ghost color}}\n|ja=いましめられしフーパ \'\'Bound Hoopa\'\'\n|fr=Hoopa Enchaîné\n|de=Gebanntes Hoopa\n|it=Hoopa Vincolato\n|ko=굴레에 빠진 후파 \'\'Gulle-e Bbajin Hoopa\'\'\n|es=Hoopa Contenido\n}}\n| style="vertical-align:top" |\n\'\'Hoopa Unbound\'\'\n{{langtable\n|color={{psychic color}}|bordercolor={{dark color}}\n|ja=ときはなたれしフーパ \'\'Released Hoopa\'\'\n|da=Frie Hoopa\n|nl=Hoopa Unbound\n|fi=Vapauttaa Hoopa\n|fr=Hoopa Déchaîné\n|de=Entfesseltes Hoopa\n|it=Hoopa Libero\n|ko=굴레를 벗어난 후파 \'\'Gulle-reul Beos-eonan Hoopa\'\'\n|pt_br=Hoopa Libertado\n|no=Ubundne Hoopa\n|ru=Свободный Хуппа \'\'Svobodnyy Khoopa\'\'\n|es=Hoopa Desatado\n|sv=Hoopa Unbound\n}}\n|}{{-}}\n\n==Related articles==\n* [[Hoopa (anime)]]\n\n==External links==\n\n{{Legendary Pokémon}}\n{{EventExclusive}}\n\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Psychic|type2=ghost}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Psychic|prevnum=719|prev=Diancie|nextnum=721|next=Volcanion}}\n|}\n{{Project Pokédex notice}}\n\n[[Category:Body style 06 Pokémon]]<!--Hoopa Unbound-->\n[[Category:Mythical Po